Real GNSS data fixtures
=======================

These two files are genuine GNSS data, included so the parsers are validated
against real broadcast/precise products rather than only self-authored samples
(see tests/igs_real_data.rs). They are not part of the Kshana source and are not
shipped in the published crates/packages — they exist only for the test suite.

BRDM00DLR_R_20130010000_01D_MN.rnx
  A RINEX 3.02 mixed (multi-GNSS) broadcast navigation file for 2013-01-01,
  produced by the DLR/TUM CONGO + IGS MGEX tracking effort
  (O. Montenbruck, DLR; P. Steigenberger, TUM). GNSS broadcast ephemerides are
  open data distributed by the International GNSS Service (IGS).

igs_sample.sp3
  A RINEX/SP3-c precise-orbit excerpt for 2017-02-14 (IGS14 frame), the first
  epoch of an IGS combined orbit product. The second epoch is truncated; the
  file exercises the SP3 reader. IGS products are openly available.

Both files were obtained from the test corpus of the georinex project
(https://github.com/geospace-code/georinex, BSD-3-Clause, M. Hirsch), which
redistributes them for testing. The underlying data are the property of, and
courtesy of, the IGS and the contributing analysis centres (DLR/TUM). See
https://igs.org for the IGS data and product use terms.
